## 12. TABLE DESIGN
### Collection: notes
| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| id | string | Unique Note ID |
| uid | string | User ID |
| title | string | Note Title |
| content | string | Markdown Content |
| updatedAt | number | Timestamp |
| dueDate | number | Optional Deadline |
| isPinned | boolean | Priority Status |

---

## 13. SAMPLE CODING
```typescript
// Example of Note Update Logic with Firestore Sync
const updateNote = async (id: string, updates: Partial<Note>) => {
  const updatedAt = Date.now();
  setNotes(prev => prev.map(n => n.id === id ? { ...n, ...updates, updatedAt } : n));

  if (user) {
    try {
      const noteRef = doc(db, 'notes', id);
      await setDoc(noteRef, { ...updates, updatedAt, uid: user.uid }, { merge: true });
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('Failed to sync note update:', err);
    }
  }
};
```

---

## 14. SAMPLE OUTPUT
The application displays a polished dashboard with a readiness score, a sidebar for navigation, and interactive modules for learning and testing. The notepad features a clean editor with a real-time Markdown preview and a date-time picker for task management.
